text: Audrey McInnis is a former Jamaican cricketer who played for Jamaica in three Women's ODIs as a part of the inaugural Women's Cricket World Cup in 1973. She made her Women's One Day International debut against Trinidad and Tobago in a group stage match during the 1973 Women's Cricket World Cup. == References == == External links == * Category:Date of birth missing (living people) Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Possibly living people Category:Jamaican women cricketers Category:West Indian women cricketers
